	<p><blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />Will they &quot;upgrade&quot; tech so they can hire less (automating the process) or are we counting on them getting the job done the old fashion way with man-power? <hr size="1" /></blockquote>If I'm a CEO and I answer only to my stock holders I am going to make my company more efficient. If that takes cutting back on people then that's what I would do. As far as the overall economy, thats not my problem as a CEO, that doesn't help me keep my job.  This tax cut could accelerate the rate of people losing their jobs. <br />
<br />
There needs to be a fundamental rethinking of our economy in order to put people back in the workplace. Tax cuts are not the answer. They put more money back in the economy, but this doesn't provide more jobs, it only provides more money.<br />
<br />
I heard an economist saying on TV that the reason people aren't buying new cars is because the cars are being made better now and people don't need new ones. The reason they aren't buying new homes is because they already have bought their homes.</p>
	
	
	
	
	
