	<!-- message -->
	<p>More from the fundamental flaws area. <br />
I was in the DMV today to transfer my license from one car to another. It renews next month. Rather than doing renewing it today they told me they could not do that because their computers will only let me do it next month. Now I have to visit the DMV twice to do two tasks rather than doing two tasks at once. Speaking of their computers they were still in DOS, which I'm sure isn't the most efficient system for running a business.<br />
<br />
Its fairly obvious that government employees only have to do their 8 hours a day and go home. There are no rewards for efficiency or any ability to get things done more efficiently. If they were more efficient our tax dollars would be much better used. That is why some people have outsourced some of the government jobs.  I have proposed on here and I still believe that government agencies need to develop their own sources of income. As it is they are tax based and not based upon performing competitively. A system of using tax dollars to ween agencies off of reliance upon tax dollars and into a self-sufficient entity should start occurring in my opinion. The post office whether we like it or not does more for each citizen and more timely and it does it better than most organizations. Why? Because it is self-sufficient.</p>
	
	
	
	
	
