	<!-- message -->
	<p>Lat, I am truly glad we have some common ground to work from.<br />
<br />
As far as <i>isolationism</i> goes, that really isn't what I would propose, too.<br />
<br />
Rather, we could afford more technology for a rapidly mobile force if we weren't paying for large lease deals for military bases to foreign countries. Another considertion is that long gone are the days of needing to mobilize forces against traditional military targets. Especially when dealing with &quot;terror&quot; organizations, aka mobile guerilla units. I agree with Rummy that we need a light, highly manuverable, hard hitting, military where we can deploy and strike where needed in short notice.<br />
<br />
I disagree that we should have our military in every theatre of the world ready to launch. To me that is just another form of &quot;world police&quot; and I think it is high time for the US to get out of Nation building.<br />
<br />
I nearly forgot to address your tax question...<br />
<br />
I would increase taxes on all tax brackets. The increases would be commensurate with savings from cutting beauracracies like the Office of Homeleand Security, the IRS, the DoD, and Pentagon (note I am not saying cut the size of the Military &quot;grunts&quot; down). The point of the increase while cutting is to pay down the defecit quickly. And I agree with you that our pork barrelling, sniveling, congressmen would fight this tooth and toenail. I understand my ideas are &quot;pie in the sky&quot;, but it sure would be great if it were done.</p>
	
	
	
