	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>Why increase taxes? Ok, so the national debt needs to be addressed (and should be). But for what else would the tax $ be spent on? More government programs? ITs one way or its the other. Either you increase taxes to pay for government programs... or you cut the programs so you can afford them with what revenues are collected.<br />
<br />
Although many do not believe this, the reason behind Bush's tax cuts is to stave off the current economic trend. For the last 15 or so years the tax payers have paid too much... And now we are seeing the results.<br />
<br />
The &quot;surplus&quot; was ungodly.. meaning we overpaid obviously. Durning the 00' election the economy had begun its downhill slide after being in a neutral state for more then a year. Itswas obvious that with all the surplus, and with the economy beginning to show signs, that we needed to get that money back into the hands of the taxpayers.<br />
<br />
No one knew that 9-11 would happen thus forcing us to spend money for the war on terror. Bush should have rethought this about his tax cuts.. I think the American people would have understood. The war in Iraq will pay for itself over time... so thats more like an investment (yeah, whatever). But this Dept. Homeland Security is a nightmare! I honeslty cannot see betterment of protection coming from this thing.. good grief!</p>
	
	
	
	
	
